  Scenario: define and use user defined literal
    Given defined US dollar money object with the following regex
    """
    ^\$\d+
    """
    When evaluate by:
    """
    $1
    """
    Then the result should:
    """
      class.simpleName: 'USDollar'
    """

  Scenario: define and not match user literal
